content.description: Sit start on the arête at the far right side of the boulder. Start with one hand on each side of the arête and climb straight up the arête.
content.location: Sit start below the arête on the right side of the boulder.

content.description: The bulge is somewhat barren, but try not to cheat on the routes to either side! Trust the crack up high to finish it off.
content.protection: 3 pads and a spotter. The topout has been cleaned out so its good, but the fall zone is sloped away.
content.location: Just left of the Exams. Start on the bulge. Small pockets and technical feet low lead into the crack up above.

content.description: Sit start 5 feet left of the arête, climb straight up on good holds.  Steep climbing on good holds.
content.location: Sit start 5 feet to the left of the arête.

content.description: Sit start below the tallest line in the middle of the boulder.  Climb straight up and top out finishing slightly to the right. Uses a sharp crimp at the crux.
content.location: Sit start below the tallest line in the middle of the boulder.  Shares the start with Entrance Exam.

content.description:
Although tall and scary looking, this is a classic high ball and feels very secure on every move.  I was surprised how many times I had walked past this one before climbing it to find it was one of the best jug halls in the park.

 Sit start for extra or just start on the big pocket center face.  Work your way up to nice juggy knob. The crux is pulling off of this knob and moving past the "do not fall" zone to a deep pocket and then up and over the top out.
content.location: This climb is between "Too Much Adderall" and "Entrance Exam".  The start is almost the same start as "Too Much Adderall' and branches right into a jug then straight up the face.

content.description: Same start as Final Exam, but bail out left at the top, avoiding the crux of final exam.
content.location: Shares start with Final Exam. Sit start below the tallest point in the middle of the boulder.

content.description: Sit start just left of the arête, climb straight up just to the left of the arête. Good holds on steep rock, fun problem.
content.location: Sit start a few feet to the left of the arête on the right side of the boulder.

content.description: Start in the hueco on the far right of the Freshman Boulder and traverse left, transitioning onto Community College Boulder. Avoid using the seam along the bottom for an added challenge. Finish in the hueco on the far left.
content.protection: One or more pads, and a spotter to move them
content.location: Straight up the access trail. Extends the full length of Freshman and Community College Boulders.

content.description: Sit start using an undercling.  Move straight up on mostly good holds to the topout.
content.location: Sit start in the middle of the right hand side of the Freshman boulder.

content.description: This is the steepest boulder at Joinerville. It features several easy/moderate problems with fun movement on steep rock and a couple of harder problems with smaller (somewhat sharp) holds.
